Fight For Love (Yuen Biao, 2007)

Plot: This film is told in flashback, as a martial arts master (Yuen Biao) looks back over his life and career leading up to his becoming the trainer of a top-ranking student. 

Overview: The boxer stood on the stage fighting for his dream, besides him stood his coach. This was the scene which, without love, would never had existed. Siu Dung was a very talented lad in sports. His father, Tin Ming, a boxer as well, nourished him well. Siu Dung&amp;#039;s mother, Gung Man objected Siu Dung in developing his skills in boxing, instead, she forced him to learn music. Right next to the music room was the martial arts room, this made Siu Dung much more difficult to concentrate in learning something he did not really interested in, after a long and harsh way, Siu Dung finally moved the martial arts master, Heung Dung, to accept him as his student, but no one would ever had expected that his would brought our a very touching story behind Siu Dun&amp;#039;g parents and his master... 

